   {:e #blake3 "fe3480f5326cec4cb49ed526b03e3ef80e5c8fc2ffc71c5d73317aa337f4ecc8" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "The invariant registry in manifest.yaml defines 23 invariants (INV-001 through INV-023) organized across 4 domains: core (INV-001 to INV-010, INV-017 to INV-020), modularization (INV-011 to INV-016), and drift (INV-021 to INV-023). Each invariant has a single owner module. Modules declare which invariants they MAINTAIN vs INTERFACE with.; The drift-management module (INV-021/022/023, ADR-012/013/014) is the newest addition. It defines: Drift Detection Completeness (every drift form detectable), Reconciliation Monotonicity (drift only decreases), and Brownfield Convergence (constructive procedure from total drift to zero). This module bridges the meta-spec with the ddis CLI toolchain.; The meta-spec uses a two-tier mode: constitution + largest module must fit within target_lines (4000) with a hard ceiling of 5000. This is the CONTEXT BUDGET concept - specs must be loadable in a single LLM context window. The manifest tracks actual line counts per module and bundle (constitution + module) sizes.; Session entity: :task/t-ae0d1671; The ddis-modular project has a parent-child spec relationship. manifest.yaml defines the meta-spec (DDIS standard itself). Child specs (like ddis-cli-spec) have parent_spec: ddis-modular. The meta-spec defines WHAT a well-formed DDIS spec is; child specs are instances. This is analogous to a type system for specifications.; Session entity: :task/t-b64e4663; Session entity: :task/t-04403285; ddis-modular is a 5-module meta-specification (DDIS v3.0) that defines HOW to write DDIS specifications. It has: constitution/system.md (537 lines), modules/core-standard.md (894), modules/element-specifications.md (918), modules/modularization.md (855), modules/guidance-operations.md (620), modules/drift-management.md (new). The manifest.yaml is the single source of truth for module composition.; Session entity: :task/t-e30d7a19; Session entity: :task/t-caa5b57a; Session entity: :task/t-15c3e555; Session entity: :session/s-1774293306; Each module declares negative_specs - explicit DON'T constraints. For example, core-standard: 'Must NOT define invariants without violation scenarios', 'Must NOT create strawman ADRs'. This is meta-level quality assurance - the meta-spec constrains what well-formed specs look like." :op :assert}
